{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869695351,"sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a15123a0011w7m7dJuvsXQsy","messageID":"msg_d7a1506f60010oV8fOXSjn4kdC","sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d673ec7096dc4a78b453113f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775869695344,"end":1775869695349}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869696301,"sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1515dd001qDGW8QNOxJAJXp","messageID":"msg_d7a1506f60010oV8fOXSjn4kdC","sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6301c43728a34b41932ff6bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n8: \n9: 1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n10: 2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n11: 3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n12: 4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n13: 5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 System Context\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                         User Application                            │\n20: │  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │\n21: │  │   CodeInterpreterClient   │   │    AgentRuntimeClient       │   │\n22: │  │   (High-level facade)     │   │    (High-level facade)      │   │\n23: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n24: │              │                                   │                   │\n25: │  ┌───────────▼───────────────┐   ┌──────────────▼──────────────┐   │\n26: │  │   ControlPlaneClient      │   │   CodeInterpreterDataPlane  │   │\n27: │  │   (Workload Manager)      │   │   AgentRuntimeDataPlane     │   │\n28: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n29: └──────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────┘\n30:                │                                  │\n31:                ▼                                  ▼\n32:     ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────┐\n33:     │  Workload Manager    │          │  Router (Data Plane)   │\n34:     │  (Control Plane API) │          │  /v1/namespaces/...    │\n35:     └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────┘\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n39: \n40: - **No single `Configuration` class**: Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across client constructors.\n41: - **Context manager support**: All clients support `with` statement for proper resource cleanup.\n42: - **Session header convention**: Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router requests.\n43: - **Timeout safety**: Read timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n44: - **Connection pooling**: `HTTPAdapter` with configurable pool size for all HTTP sessions.\n45: \n46: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n47: \n48: ```\n49: sdk-python/\n50: ├── pyproject.toml                          # Package metadata, dependencies\n51: ├── agentcube/\n52: │   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n53: │   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient (high-level facade)\n54: │   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient (high-level facade)\n55: │   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n56: │   ├── clients/\n57: │   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports: ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n58: │   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager HTTP)\n59: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n60: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n61: │   └── utils/\n62: │       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n63: │       ├── http.py                         # create_session()\n64: │       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file()\n65: │       └── log.py                          # get_logger()\n66: ├── examples/\n67: │   ├── basic_usage.py\n68: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py\n69: ├── scripts/\n70: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py\n71: └── tests/\n72:     ├── test_code_interpreter.py\n73:     ├── test_agent_runtime.py\n74:     ├── test_control_plane.py\n75:     ├── test_data_plane.py\n76:     └── test_exceptions.py\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n80: \n81: ```toml\n82: dependencies = [\n83:     \"requests\",\n84:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n85:     \"cryptography\",\n86: ]\n87: \n88: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n89: \n90: [build-system]\n91: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n92: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n93: \n94: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n95: where = [\".\"]\n96: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n97: namespaces = false\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 2. Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n105: \n106: ```\n107: Exception\n108: └── AgentCubeError (base for all SDK exceptions)\n109:     ├── CommandExecutionError (non-zero exit code from remote command)\n110:     │   Attributes: exit_code, stderr, command\n111:     │   Message: \"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n112:     ├── SessionError (session creation/management failures)\n113:     └── DataPlaneError (data plane operation failures)\n114: ```\n115: \n116: **Design Notes:**\n117: - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules.\n118: - Core clients raise `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n119: \n120: ### 2.2 Client Instance State\n121: \n122: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n123: | Field | Type | Source |\n124: |-------|------|--------|\n125: | `name` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n126: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n127: | `ttl` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `3600`) |\n128: | `verbose` | `bool` | Constructor arg (default: `False`) |\n129: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n130: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n131: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n132: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Arg or from `create_session()` |\n133: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Created in `_init_data_plane()` |\n134: \n135: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n136: | Field | Type | Source |\n137: |-------|------|--------|\n138: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n139: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n140: | `timeout` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `120`) |\n141: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Constructor arg (default: `5.0`) |\n142: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n143: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n144: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | From `bootstrap_session_id()` |\n145: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n146: \n147: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n148: | Field | Type | Source |\n149: |-------|------|--------|\n150: | `base_url` | `str` | Arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n151: | `auth_token` | `str` | Arg or SA token file |\n152: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n153: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n154: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n155: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n156: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n157: \n158: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n159: | Field | Type | Source |\n160: |-------|------|--------|\n161: | `session_id` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n162: | `base_url` | `str` | Explicit arg or `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n163: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n164: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n165: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n166: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n167: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n168: \n169: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n170: | Field | Type | Source |\n171: |-------|------|--------|\n172: | `SESSION_HEADER` | `str` | Class constant: `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n173: | `router_url` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n174: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n175: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n176: | `base_url` | `str` | `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n177: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n178: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n179: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n180: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n181: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 3. API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### 3.1 HTTP Utilities\n188: \n189: #### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n190: \n191: ```python\n192: def create_session(\n193:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n194:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n195: ) -> requests.Session:\n196:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n197: ```\n198: \n199: - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://`\n200: - Default pool: 10 connections, max size 10\n201: \n202: #### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n206:     \"\"\"Read and strip token from file. Returns '' on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: #### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n213:     \"\"\"Create a configured logger.\"\"\"\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### 3.2 Control Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n217: \n218: #### Constructor Resolution\n219: \n220: | Setting | Primary | Fallback |\n221: |---------|---------|----------|\n222: | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n223: | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n224: \n225: #### HTTP Endpoints\n226: \n227: | Method | Path | Body | Response | Notes |\n228: |--------|------|------|----------|-------|\n229: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"...\"}}` | Returns `sessionId` |\n230: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 2xx success, 404 = success | 404 treated as success |\n231: \n232: #### Methods\n233: \n234: ```python\n235: class ControlPlaneClient:\n236:     def __init__(\n237:         self,\n238:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n239:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n240:         timeout: int = 120,\n241:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n242:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n243:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n244:     )\n245: \n246:     def create_session(\n247:         self,\n248:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n249:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n250:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n251:         ttl: int = 3600,\n252:     ) -> str:\n253:         \"\"\"Create session, return session_id. Raise ValueError if sessionId absent.\"\"\"\n254: \n255:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n256:         \"\"\"Delete session. Return True on success or 404, False on other failures.\"\"\"\n257: \n258:     def close(self) -> None:\n259:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n260: ```\n261: \n262: **Headers:**\n263: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n264: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n265: \n266: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple on each request\n267: \n268: ### 3.3 Code Interpreter Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n269: \n270: #### Base URL Construction\n271: \n272: ```python\n273: if base_url is None:\n274:     base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n275:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: #### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n279: \n280: | Method | Path | Body | Notes |\n281: |--------|------|------|-------|\n282: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = `timeout_value + 2.0` |\n283: | `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | JSON body |\n284: | `POST` | `api/files` | multipart `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload |\n285: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`, `stream=True` |\n286: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` | List files |\n287: \n288: #### Methods\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n292:     def __init__(\n293:         self,\n294:         session_id: str,\n295:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n296:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n297:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n298:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n299:         timeout: int = 120,\n300:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n301:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n302:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n303:     )\n304: \n305:     def _request(\n306:         self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs\n307:     ) -> requests.Response:\n308:         \"\"\"Internal HTTP request helper. Sets Content-Type: application/json when body is set.\"\"\"\n309: \n310:     def execute_command(\n311:         self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None\n312:     ) -> str:\n313:         \"\"\"Execute command. Raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n314: \n315:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n316:         \"\"\"Execute code. Python variants write timestamped .py file first.\"\"\"\n317: \n318:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n319:         \"\"\"Write file content (base64 encoded).\"\"\"\n320: \n321:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n322:         \"\"\"Upload file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n323: \n324:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n325:         \"\"\"Download file with streaming.\"\"\"\n326: \n327:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n328:         \"\"\"List files at path.\"\"\"\n329: \n330:     def close(self) -> None:\n331:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Headers:**\n335: - Default session: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` (when `body` is set in `_request`)\n337: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n338: \n339: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n340: \n341: #### `execute_command` Timeout Logic\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n345: # PicoD timeout string\n346: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"\n347: # Read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n348: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\n349: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n350: ```\n351: \n352: #### `run_code` Python Execution Path\n353: \n354: - Languages: `python`, `py`, `python3`\n355: - Writes timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n356: - Executes `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n357: \n358: ### 3.4 Agent Runtime Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n359: \n360: #### Base URL Construction\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n364: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n365: ```\n366: \n367: #### HTTP Endpoints\n368: \n369: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n370: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n371: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers only | — |\n372: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n373: \n374: #### Methods\n375: \n376: ```python\n377: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n378:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n379: \n380:     def __init__(\n381:         self,\n382:         router_url: str,\n383:         namespace: str,\n384:         agent_name: str,\n385:         timeout: int = 120,\n386:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n387:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n388:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n389:     )\n390: \n391:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n392:         \"\"\"GET base_url, read x-agentcube-session-id header. Raise ValueError if missing.\"\"\"\n393: \n394:     def invoke(\n395:         self,\n396:         session_id: str,\n397:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n398:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n399:     ) -> requests.Response:\n400:         \"\"\"POST JSON payload with session header.\"\"\"\n401: \n402:     def close(self) -> None:\n403:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` defaults to `self.timeout` (120)\n407: \n408: ### 3.5 High-Level Facades\n409: \n410: #### `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n411: \n412: ```python\n413: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n414:     def __init__(\n415:         self,\n416:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n417:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n418:         ttl: int = 3600,\n419:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n420:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n421:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n422:         verbose: bool = False,\n423:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n424:     )\n425: \n426:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n427:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n428:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n429:     def stop(self) -> None\n430:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n431:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n432:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n433:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n434:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n435:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n436: ```\n437: \n438: **Lifecycle:**\n439: 1. If `session_id` provided: reuse it, skip control plane\n440: 2. If `session_id` not provided: call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, then `_init_data_plane()`\n441: 3. On `_init_data_plane()` failure: log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n442: \n443: #### `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n444: \n445: ```python\n446: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n447:     def __init__(\n448:         self,\n449:         agent_name: str,\n450:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n451:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n452:         verbose: bool = False,\n453:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n454:         timeout: int = 120,\n455:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n456:     )\n457: \n458:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n459:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n460:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n461:     def close(self) -> None\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **Lifecycle:**\n465: 1. If `session_id` not provided: call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()`\n466: 2. `invoke()` requires `session_id` to be set, else `ValueError`\n467: \n468: ### 3.6 Public Package Surface\n469: \n470: ```python\n471: # agentcube/__init__.py\n472: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n473: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n474: \n475: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n476: ```\n477: \n478: ```python\n479: # agentcube/clients/__init__.py\n480: __all__ = [\n481:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n482:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n483:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n484: ]\n485: ```\n486: \n487: **Note:** Only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` are exported from the root package. Data plane and control plane clients are internal implementation details accessible via `agentcube.clients.*`.\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## 4. Configuration Summary\n492: \n493: | Component | Resolved Settings |\n494: |-----------|-------------------|\n495: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n496: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n497: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n498: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n499: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ## 5. Error Handling\n504: \n505: ### 5.1 Error Classification\n506: \n507: | Scenario | Exception | Source |\n508: |----------|-----------|--------|\n509: | Router URL missing | `ValueError` | `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n510: | Session ID bootstrap missing header | `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` |\n511: | Invoke without session | `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` |\n512: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` |\n513: | Create session missing sessionId | `ValueError` | `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` |\n514: | Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (not exception) | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n515: | Delete session other failure | Logs, returns `False` | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n516: | Data plane init failure | Logs warning, cleanup, re-raise | `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()` |\n517: | HTTP errors | `requests.HTTPError` or similar | `requests` library |\n518: \n519: ### 5.2 Timeout Strategy\n520: \n521: | Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout | Notes |\n522: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|-------|\n523: | Control Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n524: | Code Interpreter Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n525: | `execute_command` | `5.0s` | `timeout_value + 2.0s` | Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout |\n526: | Agent Runtime Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n527: \n528: **Timeout tuple format:** `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` passed to `requests`\n529: \n530: ### 5.3 Exception Flow\n531: \n532: ```\n533: ValueError                    ← Configuration errors, missing session, missing headers\n534: CommandExecutionError         ← Non-zero exit code from remote command\n535: requests.RequestException     ← HTTP failures (connection errors, timeouts)\n536: requests.HTTPError            ← Non-2xx responses (if raised)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 6. Implementation Notes\n542: \n543: ### 6.1 Session Header Consistency\n544: \n545: All Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n546: \n547: - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n548: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`, set explicitly on each `POST` request\n549: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` set explicitly on the request (no JSON Content-Type)\n550: \n551: ### 6.2 Timeout Tuple Logic\n552: \n553: For `execute_command`:\n554: \n555: ```python\n556: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n557: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"  # PicoD timeout string\n558: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0      # Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n559: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n560: ```\n561: \n562: For `invoke`:\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n566: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ### 6.3 Context Manager Pattern\n570: \n571: ```python\n572: # Code Interpreter\n573: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n574:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n575:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n576: ) as client:\n577:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n578: \n579: # Agent Runtime\n580: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n581:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n582:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n583: ) as client:\n584:     response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\"})\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### 6.4 Data Plane Init Failure Cleanup\n588: \n589: ```python\n590: def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n591:     try:\n592:         self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n593:             session_id=self.session_id,\n594:             router_url=self.router_url,\n595:             namespace=self.namespace,\n596:             cr_name=self.name,\n597:         )\n598:     except Exception:\n599:         self.logger.warning(\"Data plane init failed, cleaning up session %s\", self.session_id)\n600:         self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n601:         self.session_id = None\n602:         raise\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n608: \n609: ### 7.1 Test Categories\n610: \n611: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n612: |----------|-------|-------|\n613: | Unit tests | Individual client methods, exception handling | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` |\n614: | Integration tests | HTTP endpoint contracts (mocked server) | `pytest`, `responses` or `httpretty` |\n615: | E2E tests | Full lifecycle against PicoD | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n616: \n617: ### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n618: \n619: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n620: \n621: | Test Name | Description |\n622: |-----------|-------------|\n623: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `stop()` |\n624: | `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | Data plane init failure cleans up session and re-raises |\n625: | `test_router_url_required` | Router URL required (arg or env) |\n626: | `test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` | `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit |\n627: | `test_run_code_python_writes_file` | `run_code` with Python writes timestamped file and executes |\n628: | `test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane` | Reuse of provided `session_id` skips control plane |\n629: \n630: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n631: \n632: | Test Name | Description |\n633: |-----------|-------------|\n634: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `close()` |\n635: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID reads header, raises `ValueError` if missing |\n636: | `test_invoke_without_session` | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` |\n637: | `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` | Invoke timeout tuple construction |\n638: \n639: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n640: \n641: | Test Name | Description |\n642: |-----------|-------------|\n643: | `test_create_session_returns_session_id` | Create session returns `sessionId`, raises `ValueError` if absent |\n644: | `test_delete_session_404_returns_true` | Delete session 404 returns `True` |\n645: | `test_delete_session_failure_returns_false` | Delete session other failure returns `False` |\n646: | `test_auth_token_from_sa_file` | Auth token from SA file fallback |\n647: | `test_base_url_from_env` | Base URL from env fallback |\n648: \n649: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n650: \n651: | Test Name | Description |\n652: |-----------|-------------|\n653: | `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer` | Execute command timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) |\n654: | `test_write_file_base64` | Write file base64 encoding |\n655: | `test_upload_file_multipart_session_header` | Upload file multipart with session header |\n656: | `test_download_file_streaming` | Download file streaming |\n657: | `test_list_files_query_parameter` | List files query parameter |\n658: \n659: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n660: \n661: | Test Name | Description |\n662: |-----------|-------------|\n663: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n664: | `test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises` | Bootstrap missing header raises `ValueError` |\n665: | `test_invoke_with_session_header` | Invoke POST with session header and JSON body |\n666: \n667: #### Exceptions\n668: \n669: | Test Name | Description |\n670: |-----------|-------------|\n671: | `test_command_execution_error_attributes` | `CommandExecutionError` attributes and message format |\n672: | `test_exception_hierarchy` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError` base) |\n673: | `test_session_error_data_plane_error_defined` | `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core |\n674: \n675: ### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n676: \n677: - Mock `requests.Session` and its methods (`get`, `post`, `delete`)\n678: - Mock `read_token_from_file` for auth token tests\n679: - Mock environment variables with `monkeypatch`\n680: - Use `responses` library for HTTP endpoint contract tests\n681: \n682: ### 7.4 Example Test Structure\n683: \n684: ```python\n685: # tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n686: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n687:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client): ...\n688:     def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client): ...\n689:     def test_router_url_required(self): ...\n690:     def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n691:     def test_run_code_python_writes_file(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n692:     def test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane(self): ...\n693: \n694: # tests/test_control_plane.py\n695: class TestControlPlaneClient:\n696:     def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n697:     def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n698:     def test_delete_session_404_returns_true(self, mock_session): ...\n699:     def test_delete_session_failure_returns_false(self, mock_session): ...\n700:     def test_auth_token_from_sa_file(self, mock_read_token): ...\n701:     def test_base_url_from_env(self, monkeypatch): ...\n702: \n703: # tests/test_data_plane.py\n704: class TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n705:     def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self, mock_session): ...\n706:     def test_write_file_base64(self, mock_session): ...\n707:     def test_upload_file_multipart_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n708: \n709: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n710:     def test_bootstrap_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n711:     def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n712:     def test_invoke_with_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## 8. Usage Examples\n718: \n719: ### 8.1 Code Interpreter — Basic Usage\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n723: \n724: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n725:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n726:     namespace=\"default\",\n727:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n728: ) as client:\n729:     # Execute shell command\n730:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n731:     print(result)\n732: \n733:     # Run Python code\n734:     result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\n735:     print(result)\n736: \n737:     # Write file\n738:     client.write_file(\"content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n739: \n740:     # List files\n741:     files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n742:     print(files)\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ### 8.2 Code Interpreter — Reuse Session\n746: \n747: ```python\n748: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n749: \n750: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n751:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n752:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n753: )\n754: \n755: try:\n756:     result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n757: finally:\n758:     client.stop()\n759: ```\n760: \n761: ### 8.3 Agent Runtime — Basic Usage\n762: \n763: ```python\n764: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n765: \n766: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n767:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n768:     namespace=\"production\",\n769:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n770: ) as client:\n771:     response = client.invoke({\n772:         \"action\": \"process\",\n773:         \"data\": {\"input\": \"hello world\"}\n774:     })\n775:     print(response)\n776: ```\n777: \n778: ### 8.4 Agent Runtime — Custom Timeout\n779: \n780: ```python\n781: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n782: \n783: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n784:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n785:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n786:     timeout=300,  # 5 minute read timeout\n787: ) as client:\n788:     response = client.invoke(\n789:         {\"action\": \"long_running_task\"},\n790:         timeout=600  # Override to 10 minutes for this call\n791:     )\n792: ```\n\n(End of file - total 792 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n\n1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User Application                            │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775869696284,"end":1775869696298}}}}
