{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869822222,"sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a157288001CIOyDYos1SG295","messageID":"msg_d7a155825001KWV6ZMWfHLNeZ9","sessionID":"ses_285eb22b1ffeutnHISbHaBU4v6","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_cfd5df876d5e45cdba36334d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** manifests\n**Language:** YAML\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide the complete Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`) for deploying the AgentCube control-plane stack on Kubernetes. This includes parameterized templates for Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano agent scheduler, RBAC resources, CRDs, and a comprehensive `values.yaml` that drives all configurable aspects (images, replicas, resources, Redis connectivity, environment overrides). The chart enables one-command installation and upgrade of AgentCube with environment-specific customization, eliminating manual YAML editing.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `Chart.yaml` — chart metadata (`apiVersion: v1`, name `agentcube`, version `0.1.0`, appVersion `1.0.0`)\n- `values.yaml` — full key tree with typed defaults for all components:\n  - Global: `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`\n  - Redis: `redis.addr`, `redis.password` (empty-string defaults; user must supply at install time)\n  - Router: `router.replicas`, `router.image` (repo/pullPolicy/tag), `router.service` (type/port/targetPort), `router.resources` (limits/requests), `router.config`, `router.extraEnv`, `router.serviceAccountName`, `router.rbac.create`\n  - Workload Manager: `workloadmanager.replicas`, `workloadmanager.image`, `workloadmanager.service`, `workloadmanager.resources`, `workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n  - Volcano scheduler: `volcano.scheduler.enabled`, `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, `volcano.scheduler.image`\n- Template: `workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with health probes (`/health`), Redis env vars, `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` fieldRef, `extraEnv` support, resource requests/limits from values\n- Template: `agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with health probes (`/health/live`, `/health/ready`), `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` auto-resolution via in-cluster DNS, `extraEnv`, conditional `serviceAccountName`\n- Template: `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount, ClusterRole (agent-sandbox CRDs, AgentCube CRDs, core workloads, auth, secrets), ClusterRoleBinding\n- Template: `rbac-router.yaml` — conditional namespace-scoped ServiceAccount/Role/RoleBinding for Router secret management (gated by `router.rbac.create`)\n- Template: `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — conditional ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment (gated by `volcano.scheduler.enabled`)\n- CRDs: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` and `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` under `crds/` directory (API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, scope `Namespaced`)\n- Install command pattern: `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace --set redis.addr=... --set redis.password=...`\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Dockerfile definitions for workloadmanager, router, picod images (covered by deployment spec)\n- Makefile build/docker/e2e targets (covered by deployment spec)\n- E2E test infrastructure and Kind cluster provisioning\n- Python SDK, CLI tooling, sandbox orchestration code\n- Volcano scheduler installation outside of the optional chart toggle\n- External Redis/Valkey deployment (only connectivity configuration)\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata\n├── values.yaml                         # Default configuration values\n├── crds/\n│   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n└── templates/\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WM Deployment + Service\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n    ├── rbac/\n    │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WM SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n    ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router SA + Role + RoleBinding\n    └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano scheduler\n```\n\n**Component deployment shape:**\n\n| Component | Kind | Service | Port | Health |\n|-----------|------|---------|------|--------|\n| Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | `workloadmanager` | 8080 | `GET /health` (liveness 10s, readiness 5s) |\n| Router | Deployment + Service | `agentcube-router` | 8080 | `GET /health/live` + `/health/ready` (1s initial, 2s period) |\n| Volcano Scheduler (optional) | Deployment + Service | `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` | 8080 | — |\n\n**Environment variable injection:**\n\n| Component | Env Var | Source |\n|-----------|---------|--------|\n| All | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `metadata.namespace` (fieldRef) |\n| WM, Router | `REDIS_ADDR` | `redis.addr` values |\n| WM, Router | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | `redis.password` values |\n| Router | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Auto-resolved: `http://workloadmanager.<ns>.svc.cluster.local:<port>` |\n| WM | `extraEnv` entries | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` values |\n| Router | `extraEnv` entries | `router.extraEnv` values |\n\n**RBAC matrix:**\n\n| Resource | Scope | Conditional | Grants |\n|----------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| WM ClusterRole | Cluster | Always | agent-sandbox CRDs, AgentCube CRDs (`codeinterpreters`, `agentruntimes`), pods, secrets, tokenreviews |\n| Router Role | Namespace | `router.rbac.create` | secrets (full verbs) |\n| Volcano ClusterRole | Cluster | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | CRDs, events, pods, bindings, PV/PVC, nodes, leases, resourceclaims, nodeshards |\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n| Area | Impact |\n|------|--------|\n| **Consumers** | All deployment workflows (E2E tests, production installs, developer local Kind clusters) depend on this chart |\n| **Backward compatibility** | New chart; no existing manifests to migrate. Future changes to `values.yaml` keys are breaking for downstream values files |\n| **Dependencies** | Helm 3, Kubernetes 1.28+, Redis/Valkey instance (external), optional Volcano scheduler image |\n| **Security** | WM runs as non-root (`apiserver` UID 1000); Router runs as non-root (`router` UID 1000); ClusterRole grants broad permissions (secrets CRUD, sandbox CRDs) — least-privilege review recommended; auth token review via `TokenReview` API |\n| **Performance** | Default 1 replica per component; resource requests (100m CPU, 128Mi memory) and limits (500m CPU, 512Mi memory) prevent resource starvation; horizontal scaling via `replicas` values |\n| **Operational** | `extraEnv` arrays allow runtime tuning without chart changes; `image.tag` overrides enable canary/rollback workflows |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n| Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n|-------------|------|------|----------|\n| **Raw Kubernetes YAML manifests** | No Helm dependency; simple `kubectl apply` | No parameterization; environment-specific diffs require manual editing or kustomize overlays; no `helm upgrade` rollback | Rejected — Helm provides values-driven customization and lifecycle management |\n| **Kustomize overlays** | Native kubectl support; patch-based customization | More complex for multi-environment; no built-in rollback; values not centralized in a single file | Rejected — Helm values.yaml provides a single source of truth for all configurable parameters |\n| **Helm with subcharts (wm + router as separate charts)** | Independent lifecycle per component; versioning isolation | Adds complexity for a tightly coupled control plane; shared values (Redis, namespace) require parent chart coordination | Rejected — single chart matches the coupled deployment model; subcharts can be introduced later if components decouple |\n| **Operator-based deployment** | Declarative CRD-driven lifecycle; automatic reconciliation | Significant development overhead; overkill for initial deployment; Helm is sufficient for stateless control-plane components | Deferred — consider if AgentCube adopts GitOps patterns requiring custom operators |\n| **Helm `apiVersion: v2` (Helm 3)** | Library chart support, better dependency management | `apiVersion: v1` is sufficient for current scope; migration path exists | Deferred — use `v1` now, upgrade to `v2` if subchart/library dependencies are added |\n\n## Upstream Dependencies\n\n- Helm 3 (chart packaging and installation)\n- Kubernetes API server (CRD registration, Deployment/Service/RBAC creation)\n- Redis/Valkey service (external; address and password supplied via values)\n- Container images: `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, optional `vc-agent-scheduler` (built via Makefile Docker targets)\n- agent-sandbox CRDs (external dependency; WM ClusterRole references `agents.x-k8s.io` and `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` API groups)\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Proposal review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869822200,"end":1775869822220}}}}
